5 A BILL FOR AN ACT ENTITLED: “AN ACT APPROPRIATING MONEY FOR MAJOR REPAIR AND CAPITAL
6 DEVELOPMENT PROJECTS FOR THE BIENNIUM ENDING JUNE 30, 2027; PROVIDING FOR OTHER
7 MATTERS RELATING TO THE APPROPRIATIONS; PROVIDING FOR A TRANSFER OF FUNDS FROM THE
8 GENERAL FUND TO THE CAPITAL DEVELOPMENTS LONG-RANGE BUILDING PROGRAM ACCOUNT
9 AND A TRANSFER OF FUNDS FROM THE GENERAL FUND TO A STATE SPECIAL REVENUE FUND
10 FUNDS; CREATING THE BETTER LOCAL BRIDGE FUND ACCOUNT; PROVIDING FOR A MODIFICATION
11 TO THE LONG-RANGE BUILDING PROGRAM; INCREASING CERTAIN VALUE THRESHOLDS FROM
12 $150,000 TO $300,000; PROVIDING RULEMAKING AUTHORITY; ESTABLISHING REPORTING
13 REQUIREMENTS; AMENDING SECTIONS 17-7-201, 17-7-202, 17-7-210, AND 17-7-223, MCA; AMENDING
14 SECTION 14(1), CHAPTER 762, LAWS OF 2023, AND SECTION 3, CHAPTER 763, LAWS OF 2023; AND
15 PROVIDING AN IMMEDIATE EFFECTIVE DATE.”
16
17 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF MONTANA:
18
19 NEW SECTION. Section 1. Definitions. For the purposes of [sections 1 through 10], unless
20 otherwise stated, the following definitions apply:
21 (1) "Authority only" means approval provided by the legislature to expend money that does not
22 require an appropriation, including grants, donations, auxiliary funds, proprietary funds, nonstate funds, and
23 university funds.
24 (2) "Capital development" has the same meaning as provided in 17-7-201(2).
25 (3) "Capital project" means the planning, design, renovation, construction, alteration, replacement,
26 furnishing, repair, improvement, site, utility, or land acquisition project provided for in [sections 1 through 10].
27 (4) "LRBP capital development" means the long-range building program capital developments
28 account in the capital projects fund type provided for in 17-7-209.
