9 NEW SECTION. Section 16. Better local bridge fund state special revenue account --
10 rulemaking. (1) There is an account in the state special revenue fund provided for in 17-2-102 to be known as
11 the better local bridge fund account.
12 (2) There must be deposited in the account money received pursuant to 61-3-321.
13 (3) The money in the account may be used for:
14 (a) grants to local government for the costs associated with engineering and construction of local,
15 off-system bridges; and
16 (b) administrative costs for the department, not to exceed 5% of revenue received.
17 (4) Grants to local governments must include no less than 20% local matching funds.
18 (5) The department shall enact rules for distribution of annual grants to local governments.
19
20 NEW SECTION. Section 17. Transfer of funds. (1) By June 30, 2027, the department of
21 administration shall transfer $150 million from the general fund to the capital developments long-range building
22 program account established in 17-7-209.
23 (2) BY JULY 1, 2025, THE STATE TREASURER SHALL TRANSFER $2 MILLION FROM THE GENERAL FUND TO A
24 STATE SPECIAL ACCOUNT WITHIN THE DEPARTMENT OF ENVIRONMENTAL QUALITY FOR THE PURPOSE OF LEAKING
25 PETROLEUM TANK REMEDIATION.
26 (3) By July 1, 2025, the state treasurer shall transfer $50 million from the general fund to the better
27 local bridge fund account established in [section 16].
